ifconfig - List IPS on system
ip addr show
ping ip - Test network packets reliability
tracert dns or ip - All hops to reach the destination and time taken for packets
netstat -antp -> Shows all tcp open ports
ps -ef | grep process -> lists process and greps it you can get process ID and use to grep in netstat


IP is for host identification
Port is for communication between services
nmap - illegal in some countries

dig dns - DNS lookup also records 

nslookup dns